    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <div type="text">
                    <opener>
                        <placeName>H. H. S.</placeName>
                        <date>15 July 1859</date>
                        <salute>My dear Sir,</salute>
                    </opener>
                    <div type="transcription">
                        <p>I have not thanked you for a paper with the act. of the Medical Meeting –
                            Poor Law Boards underpay my professions quite as badly as they do yours
                            – We have now considerable difficulty in procuring a chaplain, &amp; it
                            is only by taking a cure in addition that any one can be induced to
                            offer his services – I found the enclosed as a specimen of the return
                            invite we have received – &amp; are hoping to meet in a proper
                            manner</p>
                        <p>Yours very truly</p>
                        <p>J. Henslow</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </body>
